==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imperiality
<hw>Im*pe`ri*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Imperialities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Imperial power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An imperial right or privileges. See
<er>Royalty</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The late empress having, by ukases of grace, relinquished her
<qex>imperialities</qex> on the private mines, viz., the tenths of the
copper, iron, silver and gold.</q> <rj><qau>W. Tooke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperialize</ent>⟦br⟧
